The paper discusses the use of tabling in a planner developed in the Picat language to solve a planning problem. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category, which deals with the development of intelligent agents and systems. Additionally, the use of Prolog-like language and tabling suggests that the paper may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category, which deals with the design and implementation of programming languages. The paper also discusses the use of Monte Carlo Tree Search, which is a machine learning technique, suggesting that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The problem being solved involves transport of cargo items, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category, which deals with the design and analysis of algorithms and data structures. Finally, the paper discusses the development of a planner, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category, which deals with the design, development, and maintenance of software systems.
